Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.05,0:06:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Spooky Boogie rarely used the word "police" in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.28,0:06:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The one you talked to this morning is a different person.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.61,0:06:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The person we're after now is a murderer who kills people and takes control of their Avatars.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.37,0:06:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Our trace showed that the culprit was operating the Talisman Avatar from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.43,0:06:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,This apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.10,0:07:01.98,md,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.8\c&HB9BAB6&\frz13.8\fscx41\fscy41\b1\pos(581,332)\clip(422,350,460,380)\t(5,420,\clip(422,282,724,380))}Electromagnetic Shield in Operation
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.56,0:07:01.98,md,,0,0,0,,{\blur1.1\c&HBAC521&\fscx54\fscy54\b1\4c&HBAC521&\frz14.63\pos(610,429)}Unable to Perform Interior Scan
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.71,0:07:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Door breach.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.97,0:07:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.37,0:07:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.45,0:07:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're calling me, I'm guessing it's bad news.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.76,0:07:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry about that. Some hunting dogs got caught in the trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.46,0:07:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,About time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.07,0:07:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I can get you as many replacement proxy servers as you require, but do you still plan to continue with this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.89,0:07:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course. It is my duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.57,0:07:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you {\i1}are{\i0} Makishima's favorite.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.05,0:08:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Please don't screw up. Seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.33,0:08:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,How did you guys get out without even a scratch?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.21,0:08:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, don't glare at us like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.45,0:08:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe {\i1}somebody{\i0} here's been misbehaving lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.18,0:08:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.28,0:08:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got another victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.15,0:08:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Spooky Boogie.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.45,0:08:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We did a search on people who were in Inspector Tsunemori's class
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.71,0:08:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and narrowed it down to those who had affiliate income.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.91,0:08:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Sugawara Shouko, twenty years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.86,0:08:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The murder took place in her home and was carried out exactly like Hayama's.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.94,0:08:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We found pieces of her body in the sewer and yet her Avatar is still wandering about on the net.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.23,0:08:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The estimated time of death is before dawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.39,0:08:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,She must've gotten killed after last night's raid on Exoset.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.81,0:09:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go back to the office and rework our strategy with Karanomori.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.00,0:09:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,If this keeps up, we'll be playing right into his hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.53,0:09:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.26,0:09:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of me...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.88,0:09:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,she got dragged into this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.69,0:09:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Missy...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.26,0:09:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It was my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.43,0:09:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all because of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.74,0:09:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you view Spooky Boogie...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.14,0:09:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Sugawara Shouko... as a decoy?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.18,0:09:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.41,0:09:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you force her to cooperate?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.73,0:09:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.94,0:09:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you leak information on her to the enemy?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.29,0:09:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.49,0:09:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Then how is this your fault?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.72,0:09:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.41,0:09:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,She actually got...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.05,0:09:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. If we had caught the culprit last night,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.43,0:09:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Sugawara Shouko wouldn't have had to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.86,0:09:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The responsibility for that lies with all of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.11,0:09:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,For now, just think about fulfilling your responsibilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.03,0:09:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's catch this guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.10,0:10:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,In short, that's the only thing we can do to allow the victims to rest in peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.35,0:10:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I found another weird case.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.89,0:10:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Melancholia's Rainy Blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.38,0:10:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It belongs to an eighty-two year old man,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.23,0:10:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,but his grandson begged him to let him use his name and info.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.44,0:10:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, his grandson died in an accident half a year ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.38,0:10:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Tokitou Yuichi. He was fourteen years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.05,0:10:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But his Avatar, Melancholia, is still active even after his death.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.83,0:10:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,His grandfather doesn't even know how to access social networks.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.11,0:10:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, he thought the affiliate income was his pension.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.85,0:10:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Rainy Blue is a big community, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.67,0:10:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,More and more ghost Avatars keep cropping up...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.53,0:10:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it even possible to operate several different Avatars at the same time?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.53,0:10:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not uncommon for heavy users, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.21,0:10:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.63,0:10:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The unusual part is the acting abilities of this culprit.{until engiroku desu}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.96,0:11:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only do these hijacked Avatars manage to avoid suspicion,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.48,0:11:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,they're more popular than when their real owners operated them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.98,0:11:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,How is it that among tens of thousands of users, nobody noticed they were fake?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.98,0:11:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's not a matter of real or fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.13,0:11:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,These Avatars are idols on the net. In other words, icons.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.58,0:11:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Icons cannot exist solely through their own will.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.56,0:11:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither Hayama nor Sugawara built their reputations on their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.06,0:11:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,They were able to become Talisman and\N\N Spooky Boogie because their fans{until koto ni yori}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.37,0:11:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,idolized them based on their own distorted perceptions.{naru koto ni dekita}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.66,0:11:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The true feelings and natures of these idols are not\N\N the same as the ideals their characters represent.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.45,0:11:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\move(640,599,640,635,580,780)}So it's not surprising that a fan could do a better job
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.45,0:11:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,than the real owners of playing the idol fans expect to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.61,0:11:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you saying that the culprit is one of their fans?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.70,0:11:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Melancholia, Talisman, and Spooky Boogie.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.48,0:11:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He knows those three characters very well, to the point of being able to imitate them perfectly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.14,0:12:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The real culprit is someone whose level of activity matches that enthusiasm.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.31,0:12:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And how can we find this person?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.11,0:12:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Just how many people do you think would be fans of all three Avatars?{until to omotterun da}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.40,0:12:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We can use certain criteria to narrow things down.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.20,0:12:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,First, Talisman.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.13,0:12:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take the top one hundred fans among the regulars in his CommuField{until hyakunin ni tsuite}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.54,0:12:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and draw a graph of their time spent there per day,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.06,0:12:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,predominantly around the estimated time of Hayama Kimihiko's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.94,0:12:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like the time his guests spent there went down overall.{until ochikonderu ne, 2 lines + scene change}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.81,0:12:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That's around when Talisman's reputation went into decline.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.49,0:12:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But after that day, two months ago, it started to recover.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.00,0:12:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,At that point, Hayama was killed and Talisman was hijacked by an unknown party.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.32,0:12:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, there are some regulars who stopped coming to Talisman Saloon at that point.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.19,0:12:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,This pattern on the graph is the key.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.12,0:12:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,When Tokitou Yuichi, who operated Melancholia, died half a year ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.32,0:12:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and when Sugawara Shouko, Spooky Boogie, died the day before yesterday,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.68,0:13:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,there should be a user who showed the same pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.46,0:13:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. That's the culprit's own Avatar.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.28,0:13:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.10,0:13:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Once the culprit had hijacked the victims' Avatars,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.68,0:13:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,he no longer had to visit their CommuFields as a guest.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.45,0:13:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Well? Does anyone fit these criteria?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.87,0:13:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one person who does.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.89,0:13:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Mido Masatake, twenty-seven years old.{more like kotomine kirei amirite}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.25,0:13:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He works at a virtual sports management company.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.13,0:13:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,His last Psycho-Pass Hue Check was run four years ago at an annual checkup.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.64,0:13:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And he hasn't even run into any street scanners since then?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.40,0:13:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Each day, he'd take routes that would allow him to avoid street scanners.{until gurai ni wa}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.66,0:13:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That means he's got something to hide, huh?{>police logic}{until desu ne}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.12,0:13:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Trace his access records.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.26,0:13:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Way ahead of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.20,0:13:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,His last access was just a few minutes ago from a budget hotel in Roppongi, Minato ward.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.05,0:13:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,His home address is...{jitaku wa}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.19,0:13:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,located in Motoazabu, also in Minato ward.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.84,0:13:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspector Tsunemori, go investigate this hotel room with Kougami and Masaoka.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.03,0:13:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.12,0:14:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go to Motoazubu to investigate his home with Kagari and Kunizuka.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.07,0:14:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a dangerous character, skilled at cracking and explosives alike.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.93,0:14:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't let your guard down.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.19,0:14:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that for?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.47,0:14:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Strong alcohol is the best thing for handling illegal Holograms.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.67,0:14:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a trick you can take advantage of {\i1}after{\i0} you turn twenty.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.50,0:14:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Public Safety Bureau! Mido Masatake,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.14,0:14:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,please present your Psycho-Pass immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.11,0:14:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Please come out!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.73,0:14:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.57,0:15:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget cracking Holo-Cosplay! He can even crack interior Holo!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.74,0:15:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Ko!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.16,0:15:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What do we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.62,0:15:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Ko!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.29,0:15:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Crime Cofficient is 335.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.92,0:15:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Enforcement mode is Lethal Eliminator.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.70,0:15:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,A pain-inhibiting drug, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.22,0:15:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,He won't get far with those injuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.37,0:16:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's leave the rest to Ginoza and the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.78,0:16:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back, Mido!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.65,0:16:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.45,0:16:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.55,0:16:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.82,0:16:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm home.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.32,0:16:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.78,0:16:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys are eternal.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.59,0:16:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You were released from the chains of a physical body and polished by collective intelligence.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.44,0:16:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the souls most close to Plato's "idea".{:idea:}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.82,0:16:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,No one can look down on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.33,0:16:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't let anyone destroy your nobility.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.83,0:16:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I will...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.85,0:16:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I will protect it at any cost.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.32,0:16:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.55,0:16:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.91,0:17:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Mido.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.60,0:17:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Once I was guided by you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.80,0:17:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, together with you, I will guide people and the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.80,0:17:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You are eternal.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.18,0:17:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.96,0:17:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Couldn't you have done a better job, Mido?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.89,0:17:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a sec. What on earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.27,0:17:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There's something that I've been searching for. Something I want to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.40,0:17:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I've done whatever it takes to get closer to that goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.94,0:17:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, have you read Terayama Shuuji?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.48,0:17:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? T-Terayama?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.70,0:17:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You should read his play, "Saraba, eiga yo."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.29,0:17:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems like everyone is an agent for someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.79,0:17:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And what's more, those agents have their Avatars communicate in place of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.81,0:17:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you... Makishima?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.34,0:17:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You have a thorough knowledge of various Avatars and are able to imitate them perfectly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.76,0:18:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You can become anyone, so I was very interested in what your personality was like.{until kyoumi ga atta}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.96,0:18:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That is why I lent you my people and my assistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.18,0:18:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,S-Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.44,0:18:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Give them back to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.95,0:18:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't speak with their voices!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.69,0:18:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.53,0:18:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I see this play is drawing to a close.{until mietekita}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.58,0:18:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that we've arrived at the final act,{until kurai}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.60,0:18:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of borrowing the ideas of others, why don't you come up with an idea of your own to close the curtain?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.38,0:18:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You bastard... What are you...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.43,0:18:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You can play any character, and yet in the end it turned out that you yourself are nobody.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.67,0:18:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Your core personality is null. It's empty.{until karappo na}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.34,0:18:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have a face of your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.84,0:18:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how you could wear any mask at all over your smooth, featureless face and have it fit perfectly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.52,0:18:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up! Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.28,0:18:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's time to say goodbye, Mido Masatake.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.76,0:18:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The hunting dogs, those harbingers of death, have arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.60,0:19:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Enforcement mode is Lethal Eliminator.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.33,0:19:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Aim carefully and eliminate the target.{until kudasai}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.83,0:19:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.24,0:19:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,No one else is here...{\alpha&HFF&} right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.18,0:19:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,No one else is here... right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.29,0:19:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Then who on earth was he talking to?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.17,0:19:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You did quite well this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.94,0:19:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, it was Kougami who identified the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.58,0:19:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe he was able to understand how the culprit thought and predict his behavior so accurately.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.96,0:19:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what Enforcers do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.46,0:19:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,They can understand criminals precisely because they have the same psychological tendency as them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.60,0:20:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.27,0:20:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Kougami comforted me... and encouraged me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.48,0:20:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if he's a latent criminal,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.89,0:20:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,it's hard to think that he has the same mind as a homicidal maniac like Mido.{until omoimasen}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.12,0:20:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You're an Inspector. All you have to do is fulfill your duty as one.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.25,0:20:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Draw a line between yourself and the Enforcers.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.69,0:20:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that an ironclad rule for this job?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.09,0:20:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,No. It's my own rule of thumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.68,0:20:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.72,0:20:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I once lost a partner who made a mistake.{gay}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.58,0:20:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't stop him.{you can't stop AIDS}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.93,0:20:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want you to make the same mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.72,0:20:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a file from the Personnel Department.{until file da}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.09,0:20:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Destroy it when you're done reading.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.25,0:21:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Shinya Kougami. Enforcer. Male.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.56,0:21:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Twenty-eight years old. Former Inspector.{most obvious plot revelation ever}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.74,0:21:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.99,0:21:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,While investigating an unsolved case,\N Public Safety Bureau Special Case 102,{until sousachuu}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.94,0:21:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,his Crime Coefficient rapidly increased.{until joushou}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.62,0:21:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,He prioritized the investigation over his own therapy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.71,0:21:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,His Crime Coefficient exceeded the regulation limit and he was demoted to Enforcer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.48,0:21:47.41,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(600,2200)\blur1}It seems all fairy tales {\alpha&HFF&}are dead
Dialogue: 1,0:21:46.67,0:21:51.39,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(800,900)\blur1\alpha&HFF&}It seems {\alpha&H00&}all fairy tales are dead
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.14,0:21:56.74,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(600,900)\blur1}In a hospital ward of brick stones
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.60,0:22:01.83,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(600,900)\blur1}my voice is too coarse to sing
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.82,0:22:06.95,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(600,900)\blur1}Outside in the foggy haze
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.16,0:22:12.55,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(600,900)\blur1}a red moon glows
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.50,0:22:17.95,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(600,900)\blur1}Look at me
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.77,0:22:23.47,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(600,900)\blur1}Do not avert your gaze
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.85,0:22:27.79,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(160,160)\blur1}Behind black bars
Dialogue: 1,0:22:27.59,0:22:30.47,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(160,160)\blur1}I was born
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.27,0:22:32.91,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(160,160)\blur1}I wish there were a punishment for evil
Dialogue: 1,0:22:32.71,0:22:35.78,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(160,160)\blur1}Always I need you
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.58,0:22:38.45,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(160,160)\blur1}Now, grant us justice
Dialogue: 1,0:22:38.25,0:22:40.97,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(160,160)\blur1}before chaos takes us all
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.77,0:22:45.24,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(160,160)\blur1}Pay the price of fate and let us go together,
Dialogue: 1,0:22:44.92,0:22:50.99,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(160,500)\blur1}nameless beasts
